cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the modeling and inference of diffusion processes over networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper explicitly mentions the role of networks in the diffusion of information and influence. The second most likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a novel algorithm for inferring diffusion networks from cascade data. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper uses a mathematical model to describe the temporal dynamics of diffusion processes. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the optimization problem that arises in inferring diffusion networks and proposes a convex optimization approach. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the transmission rates of edges in diffusion networks.
